   public synchronized static IAMSDB getIAMSDB()
   {
    if(theInstance==null)
       theInstance = getInstance();
    return IAMSDBInstanceHolder.theInstance;
   }


Just make the getIAMSDB() method synchronized with a null check. Unless you are in an extremely high-load environment with strict performance demands, you&#39;ll never notice a difference. Also, it allows you to properly throw a runtime (or checked) exception when home is not available.

Another solution is simply to exclude certain classes from the filewalker fileset (a custom Ant task works nicely).

